      "source": "# QC Anomaly Detection Evidence\n\n## 1. Project introduction\n\nThis notebook provides **technical evidence for QC anomaly detection in C-Class LIMS** using **real QC data** from a LIMS-style export. It demonstrates how to inspect the dataset, engineer practical QC features, apply rule-based controls, run Isolation Forest, and convert the result into a simple risk-prioritisation workflow.\n\nThe notebook is intentionally beginner-friendly, with short code blocks, visible outputs, and markdown interpretation after each major section so it can be screenshotted directly for the report.\n"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 1,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": "Libraries loaded successfully.\n"
        }
      ],
      "source": "from pathlib import Path\nimport io\n\nimport numpy as np\nimport pandas as pd\nimport matplotlib.pyplot as plt\nfrom sklearn.ensemble import IsolationForest\n\nplt.style.use(\"default\")\npd.set_option(\"display.max_columns\", 40)\npd.set_option(\"display.width\", 140)\n"
    },
