      "source": "# Feature engineering\ndf[\"Deviation\"] = df[\"Value\"] - df[\"ExpectedValue\"]\nsafe_expected = df[\"ExpectedValue\"].replace(0, np.nan)\ndf[\"DeviationPct\"] = ((df[\"Deviation\"] / safe_expected) * 100).replace([np.inf, -np.inf], np.nan).fillna(0)\n\ndf[\"RollingMean\"] = df.groupby(\"Analyte\")[\"Value\"].transform(lambda s: s.rolling(window=7, min_periods=1).mean())\ndf[\"RollingStd\"] = df.groupby(\"Analyte\")[\"Value\"].transform(lambda s: s.rolling(window=7, min_periods=2).std()).fillna(0)\n\nmean_pair = (df[\"Value\"] + df[\"ParentValue\"]) / 2\ndf[\"RPD\"] = np.where(\n    df[\"ParentValue\"].notna() & (mean_pair.abs() > 1e-9),\n    (np.abs(df[\"Value\"] - df[\"ParentValue\"]) / mean_pair.abs()) * 100,\n    np.nan,\n)\n\n# The real ResultSet export does not include MatrixSpike sample types.\n# RecoveryPct is therefore kept for completeness but remains blank here.\ndf[\"RecoveryPct\"] = np.where(\n    df[\"SampleType\"].eq(\"MatrixSpike\") & (df[\"ExpectedValue\"].abs() > 1e-9),\n    (df[\"Value\"] / df[\"ExpectedValue\"]) * 100,\n    np.nan,\n)\n\ndf[[\"SampleID\", \"SampleType\", \"Value\", \"ExpectedValue\", \"Deviation\", \"RollingMean\", \"RollingStd\", \"RPD\", \"RecoveryPct\"]].head(10).round(2)\n"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": "### Interpretation\n\nThe rule-based section provides explainable QC evidence. Results are flagged Red when they fall outside lower or upper limits or when the source status already indicates failure. Yellow represents warning-range or warning-status behaviour, and Green indicates lower apparent risk. This is the most report-friendly layer because it is easy to justify.\n"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 6,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "execute_result",
          "execution_count": 6,
          "data": {
            "text/plain": "RuleFlag  Count\n   Green  68120\n     Red  22306\n  Yellow   9573",
            "text/html": "<table border=\"1\" class=\"dataframe\">\n  <thead>\n    <tr style=\"text-align: right;\">\n      <th>RuleFlag</th>\n      <th>Count</th>\n    </tr>\n  </thead>\n  <tbody>\n    <tr>\n      <td>Green</td>\n      <td>68120</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>Red</td>\n      <td>22306</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>Yellow</td>\n      <td>9573</td>\n    </tr>\n  </tbody>\n</table>"
          },
          "metadata": {}
        }
      ],
      "source": "# Rule-based traffic light logic\nlimit_red = (df[\"Value\"] < df[\"LowerLimit\"]) | (df[\"Value\"] > df[\"UpperLimit\"])\nwarning_yellow = (df[\"Value\"] < df[\"WarningLower\"]) | (df[\"Value\"] > df[\"WarningUpper\"])\nstatus_red = df[\"StandardStatus\"].str.contains(\"Failure\", case=False, na=False) | df[\"PrecisionStatus\"].str.contains(\"Failure\", case=False, na=False)\nstatus_yellow = df[\"StandardStatus\"].str.contains(\"Warning\", case=False, na=False) | df[\"PrecisionStatus\"].str.contains(\"Warning\", case=False, na=False)\n\ndf[\"RuleFlag\"] = np.select(\n    [limit_red | status_red, warning_yellow | status_yellow],\n    [\"Red\", \"Yellow\"],\n    default=\"Green\",\n)\ndf[\"RuleFlagScore\"] = df[\"RuleFlag\"].map({\"Green\": 0, \"Yellow\": 1, \"Red\": 2}).astype(int)\n\nrule_summary = df[\"RuleFlag\"].value_counts().rename_axis(\"RuleFlag\").reset_index(name=\"Count\")\nrule_summary\n"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": "### Interpretation\n\nIsolation Forest adds a machine learning perspective that can identify unusual multivariate patterns beyond fixed limits alone. The anomaly counts by sample type help explain which QC categories are contributing most strongly to the anomaly signal.\n"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 7,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": "Anomaly counts:\nIForestAnomaly\nFalse    94999\nTrue      5000\n"
        },
        {
          "output_type": "execute_result",
          "execution_count": 7,
          "data": {
            "text/plain": "       SampleType  AnomalyCount\n Standard samples          2869\nDuplicate samples          1908\n    Blank samples           223",
            "text/html": "<table border=\"1\" class=\"dataframe\">\n  <thead>\n    <tr style=\"text-align: right;\">\n      <th>SampleType</th>\n      <th>AnomalyCount</th>\n    </tr>\n  </thead>\n  <tbody>\n    <tr>\n      <td>Standard samples</td>\n      <td>2869</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>Duplicate samples</td>\n      <td>1908</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>Blank samples</td>\n      <td>223</td>\n    </tr>\n  </tbody>\n</table>"
          },
          "metadata": {}
        }
      ],
      "source": "# Isolation Forest anomaly detection\nfeature_columns = [\n    \"Value\", \"ExpectedValue\", \"Deviation\", \"DeviationPct\",\n    \"RollingMean\", \"RollingStd\", \"RPD\", \"RecoveryPct\", \"RuleFlagScore\"\n]\n\nfeature_frame = df[feature_columns].replace([np.inf, -np.inf], np.nan)\nfor column in feature_columns:\n    feature_frame[column] = feature_frame[column].fillna(feature_frame[column].median())\n    feature_frame[column] = feature_frame[column].fillna(0)\n\nmodel = IsolationForest(n_estimators=250, contamination=0.05, random_state=42, n_jobs=-1)\nlabels = model.fit_predict(feature_frame)\nscores = -model.score_samples(feature_frame)\ndf[\"IForestAnomaly\"] = labels == -1\ndf[\"IForestScore\"] = scores\ndf[\"IForestScoreNorm\"] = (scores - scores.min()) / (scores.max() - scores.min() + 1e-9)\n\nprint(\"Anomaly counts:\")\nprint(df[\"IForestAnomaly\"].value_counts())\n\nanomalies_by_sample_type = (\n    df.loc[df[\"IForestAnomaly\"]]\n    .groupby(\"SampleType\")\n    .size()\n    .rename(\"AnomalyCount\")\n    .reset_index()\n    .sort_values(\"AnomalyCount\", ascending=False)\n)\nanomalies_by_sample_type\n"
    },
