      "source": "## 11. Report interpretation\n\nThis notebook demonstrates that QC anomaly detection can be supported using **real C-Class LIMS-style data** rather than only synthetic examples. It also shows an important practical point: real data may mix explicit control limits, status fields, and parent-result logic. The workflow handles that by combining:\n\n- direct limit checks where true lower and upper limits are available\n- warning and failure statuses from the source system\n- statistical behaviour over time\n- Isolation Forest for multivariate anomaly detection\n- a risk score to prioritise review\n\nThat combination provides a credible technical evidence trail for the report while remaining simple enough to explain to non-specialist readers.\n"
